  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Water Resource Management Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drought affected/vulnerable households</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Physical (terracing, stone and soil bunds construction, cut-off drains, gully plugging etc.) and biological (grasses and tree planting) soil conservation measures, small scale irrigation, water supply schemes and livelihoods diversification activities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal is that poor rural communities have improved quality of life and reduce their vulnerability to water related shocks through Integrated Water Resources Management.

Objective 1: The local government offices support sustainable management and equitable use of water resources.

Objective 2: Communities enjoy efficient, effective and equitable water supply to support their domestic and productive needs and improve their health.

Objective 3: Vulnerable rural communities cope effectively with risks they face.</narrative>
  </description>
